    "title": "Congressman David Kustoff shares priorities following reelection - WBBJ TV",
    "text": "Congressman David Kustoff shares priorities following reelection 1 hour ago WBBJ Staff ,\nJACKSON, Tenn. — Following his reelection, Congressman David Kustoff joined us to discuss his priorities for the new congress.\nKustoff, who serves as U.S. Representative from Tennessee’s 8th Congressional District came home from Washington Thursday. As far as priorities for the new congress, Kustoff spoke on the economy, inflation, immigration, and the border. Kustoff shares it’s an honor to represent people’s voices from West Tennessee.\n“Every time I’m in Washington and I’m voting on whatever bill, whatever the initiative is, I’m thinking about what’s in the best interest of people back home and how do people want me to vote,” said Kustoff.\nKustoff then shared that president-elect Trump led with a vision and that the House of Representatives and the Senate need to follow through with his initiatives and priorities.\nKustoff claims that the nation is about to turn a corner.\nFor more Tennessee news, click here .\nCategories : News , Tennessee News Share this...\nemail Print Facebook Twitter Linkedin",
